[normal]How reliable is the Government’s forecast for gr[bold]owth in demand for the strategic road network? How should the Government deal with uncertainty in its forecast?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Highways Agency must liaise with local authorities on impact of strategic highway network on local development
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.9
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]The Highways Agency needs t
[normal]o liaise with local authorities and the City Regions regarding the impact on the strategic highway network of local economic development, of both housing, retail and employment locations, which all may generate additional traffic. This information should t
[normal]hen be used to inform the potential traffic growth expected within the area.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.10
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Traffic demand on the strategic network is determined by a number of factors that can determine use, and may help inform forecasts. These include:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.11
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The proposals within
[normal] “Action for Roads” indicates that road funding should be determined in five-year funding rounds. Each funding round should, like the rail industry, focus on delivering specific outputs and ensuring sustainability of the network. Regarding the forecast gro
[normal]wth, the funding rounds should collect robust data regarding demand, which can closely monitor the levels of actual demand and adjust accordingly.
