[normal]How can we improve the reliability and efficiency of travel on the strategic road network? What impact will [bold]new technology have?[bold]&#xa0;[bold] [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]- The use of system can make capacity improvements with any need for any 
[normal]cicvils
[normal] work to upgrade a junction
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.12
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The use of technology is having an increasing role and importance in maintaining the effectiveness of traveling on the 
[normal]strategic road network. This is already demonstrated in the use of “managed motorways” of using the hard shoulder during peak periods, and the deployment of VMS signs to inform road users of delay and disruption.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.13
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The wider deployment of this technology 
[normal]across the network will have benefits in terms of both capacity and flexibility at times of disruption. The deployment of technology however is much wider. The deployment for instance of Automatic Number Plate Recognition (ANPR) or Bluetooth opens up possi
[normal]bilities of monitoring traffic flows across the network. In addition, enforcement use for uninsured vehicles and speeding could potentially 
[normal]utilise
[normal] these technologies.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.14
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]At 
[normal]signalised
[normal] junctions, the upgrade of the signals to 
[normal]utilise
[normal] MOVA or SCOOT systems pr
[normal]ovides a chance to provide additional capacity to the road network at pinch points.
